  "title": "Lorry Crane Driver",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>KIAT LEE LANDSCAPE & BUILDING PTE LTD</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will deliver compost and/or operate heavy equipment such as lorry cranes and water tankers to support landscaping and building projects, ensuring safe and timely completion of tasks at the site.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive company vehicles safely and follow traffic regulations to deliver compost and materials on schedule</li><li>Operate lorry cranes to load, unload, and position materials accurately at job sites</li><li>Manage water tanker and TMA equipment to support site operations and maintain safety standards</li><li>Monitor vehicle and equipment condition daily and report any issues to maintain operational readiness</li><li>Coordinate with team members to complete deliveries and site tasks efficiently</li><li>Maintain a clean and safe work environment during all operations</li><li>Work six days a week and perform overtime as required to meet project deadlines</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold a valid Class 4 or Class 5 driving licence with a minimum of 2 years of driving experience</li><li>Maintain a good driving record demonstrating safe driving practices</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrate diligence and the ability to manage multiple tasks simultaneously to support smooth operations</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Work location: Around Singapore</li><li>Work schedule: 6 working days per week with overtime required</li></ul>",
